    <Content contentid="704" contenttypeid="LCTN" desc="Location / Locale">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p>
 Villa Asmara is situated about 100m away from the sea on Bali&rsquo;s south-west coast, just beyond the sleepy village of Cemagi. The glistening black volcanic-sand shores and rocky outcrops are also home to the small, but picturesque sea temple of Pura Gede Luhur Batungaus. While strong currents make the water here unsuitable for swimming, there are plenty of rock pools to explore and seaside walks to be had.<br />
 <br />
 This is the perfect environment to take a stroll or bike ride through the surrounding rice fields and experience the traditional Balinese way of life; you are bound to witness a village ceremony or two as you explore.<br />
 <br />
 Despite its rural setting, the villa is only 30 minutes&rsquo; drive from the many restaurants and shops of cosmopolitan Seminyak. World famous Echo Beach is also within easy reach (10 minutes by car), where guests can enjoy the laidback surfer vibe, an ice-cold beer and some incredible sunsets.</p>
]]></Description>
