    <Content contentid="797" contenttypeid="LYT" desc="Layout">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p> The energy and ambiance of Villa Asmara is evident from the moment guests enter the compound through the traditional Balinese doors and cross the Palimanan stepping stones over the tranquil fish pond. From here, the living pavilion overlooks the 17-metre green-stone swimming pool, at one end of which a large carved stone Buddha evokes a deep sense of calm.<br /> <br /> The three-storey living pavilion comprises a lounge and dining room at ground level, games room and master bedroom on the first floor, and a media room cosily housed under the soaring eaves of the roof space. A second master suite occupies a stand-alone poolside pavilion, opposite which lie the two guest bedrooms.</p>]]></Description>
